        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:40PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 639 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Pumpkin Buttes, or 25 miles west of Wright, moving
east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Tree Junction and Pumpkin Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
